18:29.967 --> 18:33.270
[Dramatic music]

18:33.304 --> 18:36.637
Remember what we talked about, Ming.

18:36.672 --> 18:39.340
Go!

18:39.374 --> 18:41.973
- Go! Go!
- What are you doing?

18:42.008 --> 18:43.941
Come on, go. Go, come on!

18:43.976 --> 18:47.080
Walter, get some speed up.

18:47.114 --> 18:49.082
Holy backseat driving, Batman.

18:49.116 --> 18:51.816
Come on, move it!

18:51.851 --> 18:53.687
Move it!

18:53.721 --> 18:55.925
There was a mountain of
paperwork we had to fill out

18:55.959 --> 18:57.627
for the insurance to race these cars.

18:57.661 --> 18:59.863
If we would've put even the tiniest scratch

18:59.898 --> 19:02.466
on one of these cars, the
stash would have a new owner,

19:02.500 --> 19:05.104
so we couldn't go over 10 miles an hour.

19:05.139 --> 19:07.642
And Walt threatened me
not to drive any faster,

19:07.676 --> 19:10.546
so, you know, I was basically
handcuffed at that point.

19:10.580 --> 19:12.385
[Laughter]

19:12.419 --> 19:15.122
Two iconic, powerful,
crime-fighting vehicles

19:15.156 --> 19:16.890
going head-to-head
for the first time

19:16.924 --> 19:18.958
in the world's slowest race.

19:18.992 --> 19:22.527
[Laughter]

19:23.528 --> 19:24.661
Faster!

19:24.695 --> 19:26.195
- I'm trying.
- Come on!

19:26.229 --> 19:27.996
We're gonna find out if this Batmobile

19:28.030 --> 19:30.564
has the bat ejector seats if
you don't be quiet over there.

19:30.598 --> 19:32.232
We can take these guys. Come on!

19:32.267 --> 19:34.632
Get moving! Get going. Look at him!

19:34.667 --> 19:36.636
He's faster than we are.

19:36.670 --> 19:38.371
We are blistering now.

19:38.406 --> 19:40.220
- Yes! Yes! Yes!
- Move it, man. Come on!

19:43.331 --> 19:46.132
Way to go, waiter!
Way to go.

19:46.167 --> 19:47.416
- Bat bump!
- You threw the race!

19:47.468 --> 19:48.834
Yeah!

19:48.887 --> 19:50.970
- The batmobile won. Barely.
- Of course.

19:51.005 --> 19:52.774
Of course the batmobile wins,
every time.

19:52.774 --> 19:54.614
It was close.
You guys barely won.

19:54.614 --> 19:55.635
I lost by a hair.

19:55.635 --> 19:58.144
You lost because
it's your destiny to lose.

19:58.179 --> 20:00.596
[laughter]

20:00.648 --> 20:01.496
What'd I tell you, boys?

20:01.496 --> 20:04.079
The batmobile
just blew you away, didn't it?

20:04.132 --> 20:05.464
I got no excuse.

20:05.500 --> 20:07.166
A win is a win.
Congratulations, Mr. West.

20:07.641 --> 20:09.112
Yeah, thank you, Mr. West.

20:09.299 --> 20:11.318
- Yes, thanks for coming, man.
- Thank you so much.

20:11.318 --> 20:12.410
- It was very awesome.
- You bet.

20:12.410 --> 20:13.795
Let me give you a ride
back to your car.

20:13.795 --> 20:15.142
I can walk faster, waiter.

20:15.372 --> 20:16.721
[laughter]

20:17.581 --> 20:19.414
That's a day
that I will cherish

20:19.449 --> 20:21.783
For the remaining years
of my life.

20:21.835 --> 20:23.284
Only thing missing would've been,

20:23.336 --> 20:26.171
if one of the shelves
in the stash opened up

20:26.206 --> 20:28.757
And you guys slid
down the Batpole together.

20:28.792 --> 20:31.676
It was everything and more
than I ever would've thought

20:31.711 --> 20:33.762
It would've been, you know,
having him in the car with me.

20:33.797 --> 20:35.797
And I'm not gonna lie, man.
It felt good to win.

20:35.849 --> 20:37.465
It felt good!

20:37.517 --> 20:39.100
When batman's your copilot,

20:39.136 --> 20:41.102
Every day's a win.

20:41.138 --> 20:43.021
Oh, we're gonna shut down
the atomic pile,

20:43.056 --> 20:44.973
Close up the batcave
for the night, kids.

20:45.025 --> 20:46.558
For Comic Book Men,
I'm Kevin Smith.

20:46.610 --> 20:48.026
- Bryan Johnson.
- Walt Flanagan.

20:48.061 --> 20:49.444
- Mike Zapcic.
- Ming Chen.

20:49.479 --> 20:52.647
Tune in next week, kids,
same bat-time,

20:52.699 --> 20:55.150
Same bat-channel. Good night.

